ugsburg confession article xxivand we on our part also retain many ceremonies and traditions such as the liturgy of the mass and various canticles festivals and the like which serve to preserve order in the church augburg confession article xxvi  httplcmsorgdocumentfdocsrclcmid  christian cyclopedia sv close communion st louisconcordia publishing house lutheran church–missouri synod    fellowship in the lords supper lcms  treatise on the power and primacy of the pope  book of concord paragraph    adopted at synod convention    ordination though an accepted praiseworthy ceremony has no command of god official missouri synod doctrinal statements archived  at the wayback machine  summary  the cooperative clergy study project  data archive  the association of religion data archives   see httpwwwlcmsorggraphicsassetsmedialcmswaabortionpdf  us religious landscape survey religious beliefs and practices diverse and politically relevant washington dc pew forum on religion and public life june  accessed online on september   at httpreligionspewforumorgpdfreportreligiouslandscapestudyfullpdf  historic archive cd and yearbook of american  canadian churches the national council of churches retrieved    lcms congregations report statistics for  lutheran church–missouri synod retrieved october      religious congregations and membership study glenmary research center retrieved    lipka michael july   the most and least racially diverse us religious groups pew research center retrieved july     us religious landscape survey religious beliefs and practices diverse and politically relevant detailed data tables washington dc pew forum on religion and public life june  accessed online on november   at httpreligionspewforumorgreportsdetailedtables  lutheran churchmissouri synod lcms american denomination profles association of religion data archives retrieved april     brief statement of the doctrinal position of the missouri synod concordia publishing house  retrieved  february    past